def parse(path):
    with open(path, 'r') as file:
        for line in file:
            yield json.loads(line)

# List of keys to check
keys_to_check = ["asin", "title", "price", "description", "also_view", "also_buy", "category"]
# Price pattern match
pattern = r'^[$,.0-9]*$'

# Select only properly formatted products
def is_properly_formatted(keys, dictionary):
    for key in keys:
        
        # Exclude nodes without all of the needed attributes
        if key not in dictionary:
            return False
        # Exclude products with incomplete features
        if len(dictionary[key]) == 0:
            return False
        # Exclude products with invalid prices
        if key == "price" and not bool(re.match(pattern, dictionary[key])):
            return False
        # Exclude non 5-core products
        if key == "asin" and dictionary[key] not in all_wanted_ids:
            return False
        
    return True

# Clean up product data
for product in tqdm(all_products, desc = "Processing Products"):
    
    # Only keep relevant also-view edges
    new_also_view = all_wanted_ids.intersection(set(product['also_view']))
    product['also_view'] = set(new_also_view)
    
    # Only keep relevant also-buy edges
    new_also_buy = all_wanted_ids.intersection(set(product['also_buy']))
    product['also_buy'] = set(new_also_buy)
    
    # Reformat price as a float
    if not isinstance(product['price'], float):
        dollar_value = product['price'].replace('$', '')
        dollar_value = dollar_value.replace(',', '')
        product['price'] = float(dollar_value)
    
    # Preprocess descriptions
    product['description'] = ' '.join(product['description']) if isinstance(product['description'], list) else product['description']
    
    # Keep only alphabetical characters & spaces
    pattern = r'[^a-zA-Z\s]'
    clean_description = re.sub(pattern, '', product['description'])
    product['description'] = clean_description

def list_of_dicts_to_bow_sklearn(list_of_dicts, feature):
    # Extract descriptions
    descriptions = [d[feature] for d in list_of_dicts]
    
    # Create CountVectorizer
    vectorizer = CountVectorizer(lowercase = True, 
                                 stop_words = 'english',
                                 strip_accents = 'ascii',
                                 min_df = 0.015)
    
    # Fit and transform the data
    bow_vectors = vectorizer.fit_transform(descriptions)

    # Get the vocabulary
    vocabulary = vectorizer.get_feature_names_out()

    return bow_vectors.toarray(), vocabulary

In [17]:
class GNNStack(torch.nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, input_dimensions, hidden_dimensions,
                 output_dimensions, num_layers, dropout, layer_type):
        super(GNNStack, self).__init__()
        
        # Define the type of graph convolutional layer to use
        conv_model = layer_type

        # Initialize a list to hold the graph convolutional layers
        self.convs = nn.ModuleList()
        
        # Add the first graph convolutional layer to the list
        self.convs.append(conv_model(input_dimensions, hidden_dimensions))
        
        # Store dropout rate and number of layers
        self.dropout = dropout
        self.num_layers = num_layers

        # Create additional graph convolutional layers based on the specified number of layers
        assert (self.num_layers >= 1), 'Number of layers is not valid.'
        for l in range(self.num_layers - 1):
            self.convs.append(conv_model(hidden_dimensions, hidden_dimensions))

        # Define the post-message-passing processing layers
        self.post_message_processing = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Linear(hidden_dimensions, hidden_dimensions), nn.Dropout(self.dropout),
            nn.Linear(hidden_dimensions, output_dimensions))

    def forward(self, x, edge_index):
        # Perform message passing through each graph convolutional layer
        for i in range(self.num_layers):
            x = self.convs[i](x, edge_index)                                                # Perform graph convolution
            x = torch.nn.functional.relu(x)                                                 # Apply ReLU activation function
            x = torch.nn.functional.dropout(x, p = self.dropout, training = self.training)  # Apply dropout

        # Perform post-message-passing processing
        x = self.post_message_processing(x)

        # Return the final layer of embeddings
        return x

class LinkPredictor(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, in_channels, hidden_channels, out_channels, num_layers, dropout):
        super(LinkPredictor, self).__init__()

        # Create linear layers
        self.lins = nn.ModuleList()
        self.lins.append(nn.Linear(in_channels, hidden_channels))
        for _ in range(num_layers - 2):
            self.lins.append(nn.Linear(hidden_channels, hidden_channels))
        self.lins.append(nn.Linear(hidden_channels, out_channels))

        self.dropout = dropout

    def reset_parameters(self):
        for lin in self.lins:
            lin.reset_parameters()

    def forward(self, x_i, x_j):

        x = x_i * x_j
        for lin in self.lins[:-1]:
            x = lin(x)
            x = torch.nn.functional.relu(x)
            x = torch.nn.functional.dropout(x, p = self.dropout, training = self.training)
        x = self.lins[-1](x)
        return torch.sigmoid(x)

def train(model, link_predictor, emb, edge_index, num_nodes, 
          pos_train_edge, neg_train_edge, batch_size, optimizer, noise):
    model.train()
    link_predictor.train()

    train_losses = []

    # Create DataLoader for positive and negative edges
    pos_loader = pyg.loader.DataLoader(pos_train_edge, batch_size = batch_size, shuffle = True)
    neg_loader = pyg.loader.DataLoader(neg_train_edge, batch_size = batch_size, shuffle = True)

    # Assuming pos_train_edge and neg_train_edge have the same length
    num_batches = len(pos_loader)

    for pos_batch, neg_batch in tqdm(zip(pos_loader, neg_loader), total = num_batches, leave = True):
        optimizer.zero_grad()

        # Positive edges
        pos_src, pos_dst = pos_batch.T

        # Negative edges
        neg_src, neg_dst = neg_batch.T
        
        # Noisy edges
        noise_edges = torch_geometric.utils.negative_sampling(edge_index, num_nodes = graph.num_nodes, num_neg_samples = int(noise * batch_size))

        src, dst = None, None
        
        if noise == 0:
            
            # Concatenate positive and negative edges
            src = torch.cat([pos_src, neg_src], dim = 0)
            dst = torch.cat([pos_dst, neg_dst], dim = 0)
        
        else:
            # Concatenate positive and negative edges
            src = torch.cat([pos_src, neg_src, noise_edges[0]], dim = 0)
            dst = torch.cat([pos_dst, neg_dst, noise_edges[1]], dim = 0)

        # Run message passing on the initial node embeddings to get updated embeddings
        node_emb = model(emb, edge_index)

        # Predict the class probabilities on the batch of positive and negative edges using link_predictor
        all_pred = link_predictor(node_emb[src], node_emb[dst])

        # Split predictions into positive and negative
        pos_pred = all_pred[:batch_size]
        neg_pred = all_pred[batch_size: batch_size * 3]
        noise_pred = all_pred[batch_size * 3:]
        
        # Create targets (1 for positive edges, 0 for negative edges)
        targets = torch.cat([torch.ones_like(pos_pred), torch.zeros_like(neg_pred), torch.ones_like(noise_pred)])

        # Calculate binary cross-entropy loss
        loss = torch.nn.functional.binary_cross_entropy(all_pred, targets)

        # Backpropagate and update parameters
        loss.backward()
        optimizer.step()

        train_losses.append(loss.item())

    return sum(train_losses) / len(train_losses)

def evaluate(model, link_predictor, emb, edge_index, is_validation, test_data, valid_neg_edges):
    model.eval()
    link_predictor.eval()

    correct = 0

    with torch.no_grad():
        # Get node embeddings
        node_emb = model(emb, edge_index)

        # Iterate over the test set
        for edge_id in tqdm(pyg.loader.DataLoader(range(test_data.shape[0]), 512), leave = True):
            # Extract batch of test edges
            test_edges = test_data[edge_id].T

            # Predict probabilities for test edges
            predictions = link_predictor(node_emb[test_edges[0]], node_emb[test_edges[1]])

            # Round predictions to get binary results (0 or 1)
            binary_predictions = torch.round(predictions)

            # Compare predictions with actual labels
            correct += (binary_predictions == 1).sum().item()
            
        predictions = None
        
        if is_validation:
            predictions = link_predictor(node_emb[valid_neg_edges[0]], node_emb[valid_neg_edges[1]])
            
                # Round predictions to get binary results (0 or 1)
            binary_predictions = torch.round(predictions)

            # Compare predictions with actual labels
            correct += (binary_predictions == 0).sum().item()
            
        else:
            # Iterate over the test set
            for edge_id in tqdm(pyg.loader.DataLoader(range(valid_neg_edges.shape[0]), 512), leave = True):
                # Extract batch of test edges
                test_edges = valid_neg_edges[edge_id].T

                # Predict probabilities for test edges
                predictions = link_predictor(node_emb[test_edges[0]], node_emb[test_edges[1]])

                # Round predictions to get binary results (0 or 1)
                binary_predictions = torch.round(predictions)

                # Compare predictions with actual labels
                correct += (binary_predictions == 0).sum().item()

    if is_validation:
        return correct / 10000
        
    else:
        return correct / (test_data.shape[0] + valid_neg_edges.shape[0])

In [94]:
final_val_accs = []

for drop_rate in dropout_rates:
    
    current_model_loss = []
    current_model_acc = []
    
    all_features = np.concatenate((in_degrees, out_degrees, prices, ratings, 
                               bow_vectors_descriptions, bow_vectors_reviews), axis = 1)
    graph = Data(x = all_features, y = category_array, edge_index = edge_index_buy)
    
    valid_neg_edges = torch_geometric.utils.negative_sampling(graph.edge_index, num_nodes = graph.num_nodes, num_neg_samples = 5000)
    
    # Create different folds of the data's edges
    transform = RandomLinkSplit(num_val = 5000, num_test = 5000, is_undirected = True, split_labels = True,
                                add_negative_train_samples = True, neg_sampling_ratio = 2)
    
    # Split node edges
    train_data, valid_data, test_data = transform(graph)

    train_data = train_data.to(device)
    valid_data = valid_data.to(device)
    
    model = GNNStack(node_emb_dim, hidden_dim, hidden_dim, num_layers, drop_rate, pyg.nn.conv.GCNConv).to(device)
    link_predictor = LinkPredictor(hidden_dim, hidden_dim, 1, num_layers + 1, link_dropout).to(device)
    
    optimizer = torch.optim.Adam(
    list(model.parameters()) + list(link_predictor.parameters()),
    lr = lr, weight_decay = optim_wd)
    
    num_epochs = 15
    patience = 3
    best_val_accuracy = float('-inf')
    wait = 0

    for epoch in range(1, num_epochs + 1):
        # Train for an epoch
        train_loss = train(model, link_predictor, torch.tensor(train_data.x).float().to(device),
                           train_data.edge_index, graph.num_nodes, 
                           train_data.pos_edge_label_index.T, train_data.neg_edge_label_index.T, 
                           batch_size, optimizer, 0)
        gc.collect()

        # Evaluate the model
        val_accuracy = evaluate(model, link_predictor, torch.tensor(valid_data.x).float().to(device),
                                valid_data.edge_index, valid_data.pos_edge_label_index.T, valid_neg_edges)

        # Update best validation accuracy and check for patience
        if val_accuracy > best_val_accuracy:
            best_val_accuracy = val_accuracy
            wait = 0
        else:
            wait += 1

        if wait >= patience:
            print(f'Validation accuracy did not improve for {patience} epochs. Early stopping...')
            break

        print(f"Rate {drop_rate}, Epoch {epoch}/{num_epochs}, Train Loss: {train_loss:.4f}, Validation Accuracy: {val_accuracy:.4f}")

        current_model_loss.append(train_loss)
        current_model_acc.append(val_accuracy)

        gc.collect()
            
    final_val_accs.append(current_model_acc)

final_val_accs = []
final_train_accs = []

for noise_rate in noises:
    
    current_model_loss = []
    current_model_acc = []
    current_train_acc = []
    
    all_features = np.concatenate((in_degrees, out_degrees, prices, ratings, 
                               bow_vectors_descriptions, bow_vectors_reviews), axis = 1)
    graph = Data(x = all_features, y = category_array, edge_index = edge_index_buy)
    
    valid_neg_edges = torch_geometric.utils.negative_sampling(graph.edge_index, num_nodes = graph.num_nodes, num_neg_samples = 5000)
    
    # Create different folds of the data's edges
    transform = RandomLinkSplit(num_val = 5000, num_test = 5000, is_undirected = True, split_labels = True,
                                add_negative_train_samples = True, neg_sampling_ratio = 2)
    
    # Split node edges
    train_data, valid_data, test_data = transform(graph)

    train_data = train_data.to(device)
    valid_data = valid_data.to(device)
    
    model = GNNStack(node_emb_dim, hidden_dim, hidden_dim, num_layers, 0.4, pyg.nn.conv.SAGEConv).to(device)
    link_predictor = LinkPredictor(hidden_dim, hidden_dim, 1, num_layers + 1, link_dropout).to(device)
    
    optimizer = torch.optim.Adam(
    list(model.parameters()) + list(link_predictor.parameters()),
    lr = lr, weight_decay = optim_wd)
    
    num_epochs = 25
    patience = 10
    best_val_accuracy = float('-inf')
    wait = 0

    for epoch in range(1, num_epochs + 1):
        # Train for an epoch
        train_loss = train(model, link_predictor, torch.tensor(train_data.x).float().to(device),
                           train_data.edge_index, graph.num_nodes, 
                           train_data.pos_edge_label_index.T, train_data.neg_edge_label_index.T, 
                           batch_size, optimizer, noise_rate)
        gc.collect()

        # Evaluate the model
        val_accuracy = evaluate(model, link_predictor, torch.tensor(valid_data.x).float().to(device),
                                valid_data.edge_index, True,
                                valid_data.pos_edge_label_index.T, valid_neg_edges)
        
        train_accuracy = evaluate(model, link_predictor, torch.tensor(train_data.x).float().to(device),
                                  train_data.edge_index, False,
                                  train_data.pos_edge_label_index.T, train_data.neg_edge_label_index.T)

        # Update best validation accuracy and check for patience
        if val_accuracy > best_val_accuracy:
            best_val_accuracy = val_accuracy
            wait = 0
        else:
            wait += 1

        if wait >= patience:
            print(f'Validation accuracy did not improve for {patience} epochs. Early stopping...')
            break

        print(f"Noise {noise_rate}, Epoch {epoch}/{num_epochs}, Train Loss: {train_loss:.4f}, Train Accuracy: {train_accuracy:.4f}, Validation Accuracy: {val_accuracy:.4f}")

        current_model_loss.append(train_loss)
        current_model_acc.append(val_accuracy)
        current_train_acc.append(train_accuracy)

        gc.collect()
            
    final_val_accs.append(current_model_acc)
    final_train_accs.append(current_train_acc)

def get_prob(model, link_predictor, emb, edge_index, test_data):
    model.eval()
    link_predictor.eval()

    probability_pairs = []

    with torch.no_grad():
        # Get node embeddings
        node_emb = model(emb, edge_index)

        # Iterate over the test set
        for edge_id in tqdm(pyg.loader.DataLoader(range(test_data.shape[0]), 64), leave=True):
            # Extract batch of test edges
            test_edges = test_data[edge_id].T

            # Predict probabilities for test edges
            predictions = link_predictor(node_emb[test_edges[0]], node_emb[test_edges[1]])

            # Append to the list of high probability pairs
            probability_pairs.extend(predictions)

    return probability_pairs

current_model_loss = []

                           bow_vectors_descriptions, bow_vectors_reviews), axis = 1)
graph_buy = Data(x = all_features, y = category_array, edge_index = edge_index_buy)

valid_neg_edges = torch_geometric.utils.negative_sampling(graph_buy.edge_index, num_nodes = graph_buy.num_nodes, num_neg_samples = 5000)

# Create different folds of the data's edges
transform = RandomLinkSplit(num_val = 5000, num_test = 5000, is_undirected = True, split_labels = True,
                            add_negative_train_samples = True, neg_sampling_ratio = 2)

# Split node edges
train_data, valid_data, test_data = transform(graph_buy)

train_data = train_data.to(device)
valid_data = valid_data.to(device)

model_buy = GNNStack(node_emb_dim, hidden_dim, hidden_dim, num_layers, 0, pyg.nn.conv.GCNConv).to(device)
link_predictor_buy = LinkPredictor(hidden_dim, hidden_dim, 1, num_layers + 1, link_dropout).to(device)

optimizer = torch.optim.Adam(
list(model_buy.parameters()) + list(link_predictor_buy.parameters()),
lr = lr, weight_decay = optim_wd)

num_epochs = 15
patience = 1

wait = 0

for epoch in range(1, num_epochs + 1):
    # Train for an epoch
    train_loss = train(model_buy, link_predictor_buy, torch.tensor(train_data.x).float().to(device),
                       train_data.edge_index, graph_buy.num_nodes, 
                       train_data.pos_edge_label_index.T, train_data.neg_edge_label_index.T, 
                       batch_size, optimizer, 0.05)
    gc.collect()

    # Evaluate the model
    val_accuracy = evaluate(model_buy, link_predictor_buy, torch.tensor(valid_data.x).float().to(device),
                            valid_data.edge_index, True,
                            valid_data.pos_edge_label_index.T, valid_neg_edges)

    train_accuracy = evaluate(model_buy, link_predictor_buy, torch.tensor(train_data.x).float().to(device),
                              train_data.edge_index, False,
                              train_data.pos_edge_label_index.T, train_data.neg_edge_label_index.T)

    # Update best validation accuracy and check for patience
    if val_accuracy > best_val_accuracy:
        best_val_accuracy = val_accuracy
        wait = 0
    else:
        wait += 1

    if wait >= patience:
        print(f"Epoch {epoch}/{num_epochs}, Train Loss: {train_loss:.4f}, Train Accuracy: {train_accuracy:.4f}, Validation Accuracy: {val_accuracy:.4f}\n")
        print(f'Validation accuracy did not improve for {patience} epochs. Early stopping...')
        break

    print(f"Epoch {epoch}/{num_epochs}, Train Loss: {train_loss:.4f}, Train Accuracy: {train_accuracy:.4f}, Validation Accuracy: {val_accuracy:.4f}")

    current_model_loss.append(train_loss)
    current_model_acc.append(val_accuracy)
    current_train_acc.append(train_accuracy)

    gc.collect()

    dst_node_idx = graph.edge_index[1, edge_idx].item()
    
    view_probability = link_predictor_view(node_emb_view[src_node_idx], node_emb_view[dst_node_idx])
    view_probability = round(view_probability.item(), 4)
    
    buy_probability = link_predictor_buy(node_emb_buy[src_node_idx], node_emb_buy[dst_node_idx])
    buy_probability = round(buy_probability.item(), 4)
    
    # Step 3: Append data to lists
    data['Edge Index'].append(edge_idx)
    data['Source Node Title'].append(all_products[src_node_idx]['title'])
    data['Destination Node Title'].append(all_products[dst_node_idx]['title'])
    data['View Probability'].append(view_probability)
    data['Buy Probability'].append(buy_probability)

edge_index_buy = []
in_degrees = np.zeros((len(all_products), 1))
out_degrees = np.zeros((len(all_products), 1))
prices = np.zeros((len(all_products), 1))

for product in all_products:
    
    for co_bought in product['also_buy']:
            
        # Construct graph
        in_degrees[asin_to_idx_map[co_bought]][0] += 1
        edge_index_buy.append([asin_to_idx_map[product['asin']], asin_to_idx_map[co_bought]])

edge_index_buy = torch.tensor(edge_index_buy).t().contiguous()
graph = Data(x = in_degrees, edge_index = edge_index_buy)

torch.save(graph, 'amazon_clothing_buy.pt')

edge_index_view = []
in_degrees = np.zeros((len(all_products), 1))

for product in all_products:
    
    for co_viewed in product['also_view']:
            
        # Construct graph
        in_degrees[asin_to_idx_map[co_viewed]][0] += 1
        out_degrees[asin_to_idx_map[product['asin']]][0] += 1
        edge_index_view.append([asin_to_idx_map[product['asin']], asin_to_idx_map[co_viewed]])
        
    prices[asin_to_idx_map[product['asin']]][0] = product['price']

edge_index_view = torch.tensor(edge_index_view).t().contiguous()
all_features = np.concatenate((in_degrees, out_degrees, prices, bow_vectors), axis=1)
graph = Data(x = all_features, edge_index = edge_index_view)

torch.save(graph, 'amazon_clothing_view.pt')

g_buy = torch.load(f'/kaggle/working/amazon_clothing_buy.pt')
g_view = torch.load(f'/kaggle/working/amazon_clothing_view.pt')
net = Network(height = "750px", width = "100%", bgcolor = "#FFFFFF", font_color = "white",
             directed = True)

# Construct graph
for e in tqdm(g_buy.edge_index.T):

    src = e[0].item()
    dst = e[1].item()
    if src not in viz_node_idx_view or dst not in viz_node_idx_view:
        continue
    
    src_title = "Title:" + all_products[src]['title'] + "\n\n" + "Categories:\n" + "\n".join(list(all_products[src]['category'])[:3])
    dst_title = "Title:" + all_products[dst]['title'] + "\n\n" + "Categories:\n" + "\n".join(list(all_products[dst]['category'])[:3])
    
    net.add_node(dst, label = src_title, title = src_title)
    net.add_node(src, label = dst_title, title = dst_title)
    net.add_edge(src, dst, value = 0.1, color = "blue", arrows = "none")
    
for e in tqdm(g_view.edge_index.T):

    src = e[0].item()
    dst = e[1].item()
    if src not in viz_node_idx_view or dst not in viz_node_idx_view:
        continue
    
    src_title = "Title:" + all_products[src]['title'] + "\n\n" + "Categories:\n" + "\n".join(list(all_products[src]['category'])[:3])
    dst_title = "Title:" + all_products[dst]['title'] + "\n\n" + "Categories:\n" + "\n".join(list(all_products[dst]['category'])[:3])
    
    if dst not in net.nodes:
        net.add_node(dst, label = src_title, title = src_title)
    if src not in net.nodes:
        net.add_node(src, label = dst_title, title = dst_title)
        
    net.add_edge(src, dst, value = 0.1, color = "red", arrows = "none")

# Save the PyVis visualisation to a HTML file
net.set_edge_smooth('dynamic')
net.show("/kaggle/working/graph_buy_and_view.html", notebook = False)
